WEBVTT

00:00.561 --> 00:02.050
<i>Previously on "The Catch"...</i>

00:02.156 --> 00:04.798
I gave him all of my
money, $1.4 million,

00:04.799 --> 00:06.658
my entire life savings.

00:06.659 --> 00:07.858
If you can't love
somebody at their worst,

00:07.859 --> 00:08.868
then you never really loved them.

00:08.869 --> 00:10.992
You're not in a relationship, are you?

00:11.109 --> 00:11.668
Are you?

00:11.669 --> 00:13.688
In a relationship?

00:13.689 --> 00:15.553
Our benefactor is expecting payment.

00:15.554 --> 00:16.728
If we don't pay...

00:16.729 --> 00:17.868
Ben: I will make enough off the Princess

00:17.869 --> 00:19.718
to cover all our debt and then some.

00:19.719 --> 00:21.648
- Who are you?
- Michael Thorne.

00:21.649 --> 00:22.808
Alice: So he's
officially Michael Thorne?

00:22.809 --> 00:24.758
He just opened three new credit cards.

00:24.759 --> 00:26.718
We'll know where he
is and what he's doing.

00:26.719 --> 00:28.858
Margot: The mark is Qasim Halabi,
the princess' guardian.

00:28.859 --> 00:30.788
I will find out who you really are.

00:30.789 --> 00:32.688
I will expose you.

00:32.689 --> 00:33.848
[Grunts]

00:33.849 --> 00:34.868
He's a killer.

00:34.869 --> 00:36.828
And you'll never catch him on your own.

00:36.829 --> 00:38.638
We were together for over a year.

00:38.639 --> 00:39.678
And you're saying that,

00:39.679 --> 00:40.868
in all that time, she
never saw the real you?

00:40.869 --> 00:42.718
If you're thinking about her,

00:42.719 --> 00:44.638
I guarantee she's thinking about you.

00:44.639 --> 00:45.698
Listen, I know you're angry,

00:45.699 --> 00:46.798
and you have every right to be.

00:46.799 --> 00:48.828
Promise me you won't
come looking for me.

00:48.829 --> 00:50.698
Alice: I won't come looking for you.

00:50.699 --> 00:51.778
Because I've already found you.

00:51.779 --> 00:53.759
♪ ♪

00:58.739 --> 01:01.858
[Alabama Shakes' "Don't
Wanna Fight" plays]

01:01.859 --> 01:04.727
Princess Zara Al-Salim of Kuroq.

01:04.729 --> 01:06.738
She's beautiful, obscenely rich,

01:06.739 --> 01:10.638
and normally surrounded
by security at all times...

01:10.639 --> 01:13.638
♪ My life, your life ♪

01:13.639 --> 01:14.778
until two days ago,

01:14.779 --> 01:19.768
when her guardian, Qasim
Halabi, disappeared...

01:19.769 --> 01:21.858
♪ I don't wanna fight no more ♪

01:21.859 --> 01:23.698
♪ I don't wanna fight no more ♪

01:23.699 --> 01:26.688
leaving Zara vulnerable to
the attentions of a man

01:26.689 --> 01:28.708
who will seduce and rob
her, same way that he did me.

01:28.709 --> 01:29.748
♪ I don't wanna fight no more ♪

01:29.749 --> 01:30.788
With Qasim gone,

01:30.789 --> 01:33.698
Zara's demeanor has changed completely.

01:33.699 --> 01:35.638
She's not just stepping out...

01:35.639 --> 01:36.858
She's inviting people in,

01:36.859 --> 01:40.728
meeting with local
entrepreneurs about investment opportunities,

01:40.729 --> 01:42.718
opening herself up in
a way that will allow us

01:42.719 --> 01:44.868
to monitor her calls,
her texts, her movements,

01:44.869 --> 01:47.738
so that we can catch
Christopher in the act...

01:47.739 --> 01:50.828
That is, if you're okay
working on this together.

01:50.829 --> 01:52.638
♪ Whoo ♪

01:52.639 --> 01:54.778
I thought you'd never ask.

01:54.779 --> 01:57.728
♪ I don't wanna fight no more ♪

01:57.729 --> 01:59.605
♪ ♪

02:00.039 --> 02:03.571
Synced and corrected by VitoSilans
- www.Addic7ed.com -

02:04.839 --> 02:06.658
How does your partner feel

02:06.659 --> 02:08.638
about working with the FBI on this one?

02:08.639 --> 02:09.638
She doesn't know,

02:09.639 --> 02:11.638
and I'd rather she didn't find out.

02:11.639 --> 02:13.698
She does not approve.

02:13.699 --> 02:16.758
She thinks Christopher's
taken too much from me already.

02:16.759 --> 02:18.758
She's not wrong.

02:18.759 --> 02:20.698
Perhaps you should let
me take it from here.

02:20.699 --> 02:21.748
No offense,

02:21.749 --> 02:24.808
but you've been after him
for two years on your own.

02:24.809 --> 02:26.848
What makes you think you
can do this without me?

02:26.849 --> 02:29.738
He's not the man you
knew. He's a killer.

02:29.739 --> 02:30.799
Alleged killer.

02:31.849 --> 02:33.718
- He's a con man.
- [Elevator bell dings]

02:33.719 --> 02:37.638
Who will stop at nothing...

02:37.639 --> 02:38.698
to get what he wants.

02:38.699 --> 02:40.639
Neither will I.

02:42.679 --> 02:44.769
♪ ♪

02:46.759 --> 02:49.718
You want to know why you
haven't caught this guy yet?

02:49.719 --> 02:51.678
- Because you're too good...
- [Chuckles]

02:51.679 --> 02:52.818
too decent.

02:52.819 --> 02:56.708
You of all people should
know how indecent I can be.

02:56.709 --> 02:58.798
You give everyone the
benefit of the doubt

02:58.799 --> 03:00.768
whether they deserve it or not,

03:00.769 --> 03:03.799
and Mr. X doesn't deserve it.

03:04.749 --> 03:05.838
You want to catch him...

03:05.839 --> 03:08.768
you need to start
thinking like a criminal.

03:08.769 --> 03:10.769
♪ ♪

03:14.799 --> 03:18.689
We'll be in touch. Thank
you both for coming by.

03:22.699 --> 03:24.709
[Door opens]

03:26.869 --> 03:27.868
[Door closes]

03:27.869 --> 03:29.668
What is it?

03:29.669 --> 03:30.688
Qasim.

03:30.689 --> 03:32.808
He never arrived in Kuroq.

03:32.809 --> 03:37.688
My brother's coming to look
for him... and to take me home.

03:37.689 --> 03:39.798
When?

03:39.799 --> 03:41.768
Within the week, he says.

03:41.769 --> 03:43.749
I'm not going.

03:44.849 --> 03:47.728
Women can work here.
They can go to school.

03:47.729 --> 03:49.758
They can go see a doctor

03:49.759 --> 03:51.778
without asking for a man's permission.

03:51.779 --> 03:54.698
Qasim was a liar and a thief,

03:54.699 --> 03:56.768
but perhaps he had the right idea...

03:56.769 --> 04:02.639
Take as much money as
you can and disappear.

04:05.829 --> 04:08.699
Will you help me disappear?

04:13.719 --> 04:15.748
In addition to our
investigative services,

04:15.749 --> 04:19.659
we also have our own
private security team.

04:20.759 --> 04:22.648
In fact,

04:22.649 --> 04:25.668
there's the head of our
security right there, Shawn Sullivan,

04:25.669 --> 04:27.819
conferring with our in-house
counsel, Sophie Novak.

04:30.709 --> 04:32.728
Who are they?

04:32.729 --> 04:35.798
That's Phillip Thompson, the
C.E.O. of Olympic Edge.

04:35.799 --> 04:36.838
The tech company?

04:36.839 --> 04:37.838
Not just tech anymore.

04:37.839 --> 04:39.668
Huge military contracts.

04:39.669 --> 04:40.869
Yeah, not just our military.

04:42.148 --> 04:43.678
You two look cozy in here.

04:43.679 --> 04:45.678
Shouldn't you be in the
Security wing, Shawn?

04:45.679 --> 04:47.749
[Chuckles]

04:48.759 --> 04:50.403
What is wrong with you?

04:50.539 --> 04:51.848
Do you not know those people are?

04:51.849 --> 04:53.838
I do. What are they doing here?

04:53.839 --> 04:55.798
They won't tell us till
we sign their NDA.

04:55.799 --> 04:57.638
They're military contractors.

04:57.691 --> 04:59.373
Are we sure we want
to take this meeting?

04:59.374 --> 05:01.848
They're military contractors.
I don't think we have a choice.

05:01.849 --> 05:03.859
♪ ♪

05:04.819 --> 05:07.778
In January 2010,

05:07.779 --> 05:10.688
a devastating 7.0 earthquake

05:10.689 --> 05:13.648
crippled the city of Léogâne in Haiti.

05:13.649 --> 05:15.638
I was there.

05:15.639 --> 05:19.638
<i>160,000 people lost their lives that day</i>

05:19.639 --> 05:22.638
<i>because first responders couldn't
find them in time.</i>

05:22.639 --> 05:23.718
[Button clicks]

05:23.719 --> 05:26.768
This is Gwen Ericsson, who, along
with Marie Sherwood here,

05:26.769 --> 05:28.778
designed our THRUsight technology.

05:28.779 --> 05:32.718
As you can see, Gwen
is.... extraordinary young woman.

05:32.719 --> 05:33.748
She's a genius.

05:33.749 --> 05:35.728
She's a beloved member
of our corporate family,

05:35.729 --> 05:37.798
and she is currently missing.

05:37.799 --> 05:40.523
She left our offices Friday night

05:40.524 --> 05:42.232
and has not been
seen or heard from since.

05:42.233 --> 05:43.678
Has anyone been to her apartment?

05:43.679 --> 05:44.648
I have.

05:44.649 --> 05:46.300
She hasn't been there in days.

05:46.431 --> 05:48.066
You've talked to her friends, family?

05:48.067 --> 05:48.668
Everyone.

05:48.669 --> 05:49.748
No ones heard from her...

05:49.749 --> 05:52.638
no calls, texts, e-mails.

05:52.639 --> 05:54.828
We've tried to locate her
cellphone, her laptop.

05:54.829 --> 05:56.678
Did you contact the police?

05:56.679 --> 05:58.748
If it was any other
project, we would have,

05:58.749 --> 05:59.858
but this is THRUsight.

05:59.859 --> 06:02.718
And THRUsight is the
reason we signed the NDA.

06:02.719 --> 06:03.718
Marie.

06:03.719 --> 06:04.808
[Keyboard clacks]

06:04.809 --> 06:07.718
THRUsight was designed to
help located disaster victims

06:07.719 --> 06:10.668
behind walls,
floors, under rubble, debris.

06:10.669 --> 06:12.638
Valerie: It sees through walls?

06:12.639 --> 06:14.678
Marie: Drywall, cement blocks, concrete.

06:14.679 --> 06:15.758
Human flesh.

06:15.759 --> 06:17.868
We can monitor your
heartbeat from 30 miles away.

06:17.869 --> 06:22.638
It can also target and
detect troops, armaments...

06:22.639 --> 06:23.678
pretty much anything.

06:23.679 --> 06:24.678
So it's a weapon.

06:24.679 --> 06:25.798
It was not designed to be, but...

06:25.799 --> 06:26.837
Potentially.

06:26.839 --> 06:28.632
I can't believe this exists.

06:28.633 --> 06:30.549
Well, we're still a few
weeks away from production,

06:30.550 --> 06:31.972
but the only person

06:31.973 --> 06:33.798
that has a complete copy of
the manufacturing specs...

06:33.799 --> 06:35.818
- Alice: Is Gwen.
- Valerie: And now she's missing.

06:35.819 --> 06:38.788
- Or she's been taken.
- Along with her laptop.

06:38.789 --> 06:39.848
Taken by...

06:39.849 --> 06:42.749
Any of our competitors, rival
nation, terrorist group.

06:43.839 --> 06:45.798
You can see why it's
essential that we find her.

06:45.799 --> 06:48.639
♪ ♪

06:49.759 --> 06:51.758
Um...

06:51.759 --> 06:54.668
The thing Phillip didn't tell you is

06:54.669 --> 06:56.708
sometimes Gwen does this.

06:56.709 --> 06:57.718
She disappears?

06:57.719 --> 06:59.788
When she can't figure something out

06:59.789 --> 07:02.638
or doesn't know the answer to something,

07:02.639 --> 07:03.678
she'll grab her laptop

07:03.679 --> 07:05.638
and go on a hike or to the beach,

07:05.639 --> 07:06.708
and I didn't tell Phillip

07:06.709 --> 07:08.678
because I thought she'd just show up

07:08.679 --> 07:10.798
[Voice breaking] like she always does.

07:10.799 --> 07:13.648
But it's been four days.

07:13.649 --> 07:15.768
I should've said something to Phillip.

07:15.769 --> 07:18.748
I just thought Gwen was being Gwen.

07:18.749 --> 07:20.658
Now, if anything's happened to her...

07:20.659 --> 07:23.808
Don't worry, Marie.
We're gonna find her.

07:23.809 --> 07:26.638
[Breathes shakily]

07:26.639 --> 07:28.728
[Footsteps depart]

07:28.729 --> 07:31.623
Ben: She wants me to help her disappear.

07:31.639 --> 07:32.728
How much money have you already taken?

07:32.729 --> 07:33.748
What are you talking about?

07:33.749 --> 07:34.808
Well, you're her financial advisor.

07:34.809 --> 07:36.798
I assume you've been
skimming off the top.

07:36.799 --> 07:38.668
That is what Qasim was doing.

07:38.669 --> 07:40.638
And rightly so.

07:40.639 --> 07:42.648
You're making me wish I hadn't shot him.

07:42.649 --> 07:43.708
I am earning her trust.

07:43.709 --> 07:45.838
You've earned her
trust. Now rob her blind.

07:45.839 --> 07:47.638
[Lock beeps]

07:47.639 --> 07:48.798
Our payment is now officially past due,

07:48.799 --> 07:50.848
so it won't be long before
they send someone after us,

07:50.849 --> 07:53.728
and when that
happens, we have two options...

07:53.729 --> 07:55.698
- deliver or...
- [Door closes]

07:55.699 --> 07:56.858
die.

07:56.859 --> 07:59.778
You've taken the
words right out of my mouth.

07:59.779 --> 08:01.625
♪ ♪

08:03.182 --> 08:06.531
We'd like to request an extension.

08:09.451 --> 08:10.450
I'm sure you would,

08:10.451 --> 08:12.201
but you know that's not possible.

08:12.202 --> 08:13.370
Then why haven't you shot us yet?

08:13.371 --> 08:14.410
Darling, she's having her tea.

08:14.411 --> 08:15.420
And it seems our benefactor

08:15.421 --> 08:17.430
has a little soft spot for you two.

08:17.431 --> 08:18.490
Well, in which
case, I'd like to explain.

08:18.491 --> 08:20.411
Let me be clear.

08:21.491 --> 08:23.540
I'm not the messenger.

08:23.541 --> 08:25.490
I'm the collector.

08:25.491 --> 08:26.520
I know exactly what you are.

08:26.521 --> 08:28.380
I know who you are, as well.

08:28.381 --> 08:30.390
You still have quite the
reputation back home.

08:30.391 --> 08:31.510
In fact, you've made it very difficult

08:31.511 --> 08:34.530
for anyone else in this
position to measure up.

08:34.530 --> 08:36.539
Have I?

08:36.541 --> 08:38.580
How much have you got?

08:38.581 --> 08:40.490
$1.5 million.

08:40.491 --> 08:41.539
Tell you what...

08:41.541 --> 08:43.510
Give it to me, and
I'll give you 24 hours.

08:43.510 --> 08:45.430
- We're not giving you anything.
- 48 hours.

08:45.431 --> 08:46.991
- Why are you bargaining with...
- Done.

08:52.461 --> 08:54.450
[Door opens, closes]

08:54.451 --> 08:56.560
Why do you insist on
giving away all our money?

08:56.561 --> 08:58.582
Did you not see the gun she left out

08:58.607 --> 09:00.440
in full view for maximum impact?

09:00.441 --> 09:02.480
You're going to have to
tell the princess that you found

09:02.481 --> 09:05.440
a fleet of private
jets for her to invest in

09:05.441 --> 09:07.440
or a château in San Simeon.

09:07.441 --> 09:09.480
She doesn't want any of
that. She feels trapped by it all.

09:09.481 --> 09:11.440
And at the moment, I know how she feels.

09:11.441 --> 09:12.560
[Breathes deeply]

09:12.561 --> 09:13.560
Then sell her that.

09:13.561 --> 09:15.440
Sell her what?

09:15.441 --> 09:16.490
Freedom.

09:16.491 --> 09:19.390
How does her writing me
a check for $10 million...

09:19.391 --> 09:20.450
$15 million just while we're about it.

09:20.451 --> 09:22.410
Well, how does that buy her freedom?

09:22.411 --> 09:24.370
<i>Because she won't be
writing you the check.</i>

09:24.371 --> 09:27.570
She'll be writing it to
the charitable foundation

09:27.571 --> 09:30.440
that she'll be putting you in charge of.

09:30.441 --> 09:31.520
♪ ♪

09:31.521 --> 09:33.510
A foundation in my name?

09:33.511 --> 09:36.470
Using your family's
money to donate to a charity

09:36.471 --> 09:37.570
supporting the
education and equal rights

09:37.571 --> 09:39.360
for women all over the world.

09:39.361 --> 09:40.410
But my family doesn't believe

09:40.411 --> 09:41.550
in education and equal rights for women.

09:41.551 --> 09:44.370
I know. They hate that.

09:44.371 --> 09:45.530
They'll disown me.

09:45.531 --> 09:46.591
That's the idea.

09:48.371 --> 09:49.490
But I promise you,

09:49.491 --> 09:51.480
if you make enough noise with
this, you'll be a symbol.

09:51.481 --> 09:53.360
You'll be granted asylum.

09:53.361 --> 09:55.761
You can do whatever you want,
you can live wherever you want.

09:56.491 --> 09:59.440
It can't possibly work.

09:59.441 --> 10:01.500
Can it?

10:01.501 --> 10:03.440
Well, in my experience,

10:03.441 --> 10:04.570
standing up for
yourself and other people

10:04.571 --> 10:07.500
is always better than running away.

10:07.501 --> 10:10.480
But you have to do it now before
your brother shows up

10:10.481 --> 10:12.471
and takes your checkbook away.

10:14.431 --> 10:15.500
♪ ♪

10:15.501 --> 10:17.410
When Gwen Ericsson was in high school,

10:17.411 --> 10:19.520
she invented a device that uses sound

10:19.521 --> 10:22.400
to determine the location of explosives.

10:22.401 --> 10:24.580
In 2010, after the Haiti earthquake,

10:24.581 --> 10:27.430
Gwen returned to the
U.S. to develop THRUsight

10:27.431 --> 10:29.520
to help first
responders locate survivors.

10:29.521 --> 10:32.460
But she didn't have any money, so...

10:32.461 --> 10:33.480
She partnered with Marie Sherwood,

10:33.481 --> 10:34.520
her best friend and roommate.

10:34.521 --> 10:36.530
Marie was finishing her MBA at Stanford

10:36.531 --> 10:38.510
when she and Gwen launched Pegasys,

10:38.511 --> 10:40.520
a tiny startup that caught
the eye of Phillip Thompson.

10:40.521 --> 10:43.440
So while Gwen was
busy engineering THRUsight...

10:43.441 --> 10:44.520
Marie was busy engineering

10:44.521 --> 10:46.450
the sale of Pegasys to Olympic Edge,

10:46.451 --> 10:48.530
giving Gwen all the
money and resources she needed

10:48.531 --> 10:50.550
to get THRUsight off her
laptop and into production.

10:50.551 --> 10:52.400
Until the night she disappeared.

10:52.401 --> 10:53.520
And according to Phillip Thompson,

10:53.521 --> 10:55.360
Gwen never missed a deadline.

10:55.361 --> 10:58.410
So we're thinking
kidnapping by a rival company.

10:58.411 --> 10:59.520
I have a list of possible candidates.

10:59.521 --> 11:01.500
Or a dictatorship or a terrorist cell.

11:01.501 --> 11:04.570
I'm looking into some of the darker
corners of the Internet.

11:04.571 --> 11:06.530
- Any luck tracking the laptop?
- Not yet.

11:06.531 --> 11:08.520
But we do have a lead on Gwen's car.

11:08.521 --> 11:10.580
Sophie was able to hack in
to her FasTrak account,

11:10.581 --> 11:13.550
and on Saturday morning, she
took Exit 76 off of 210.

11:13.551 --> 11:15.490
What's Exit 76?

11:15.491 --> 11:17.450
The San Alvarez hiking trails.

11:17.451 --> 11:19.560
Call Marie. Find out if
Gwen had a favorite trail there.

11:19.561 --> 11:21.480
Lamplight Peak. We're headed there now.

11:21.481 --> 11:22.570
Oh, and, Danny, take Shawn with you.

11:22.571 --> 11:24.360
What? Why?

11:24.361 --> 11:26.460
If we're dealing with terrorists...

11:26.461 --> 11:27.550
I can handle terrorists.

11:27.551 --> 11:29.460
Oh, he's... Just...

11:29.461 --> 11:31.021
He's bigger than you are. To be safe.

11:35.531 --> 11:38.430
Danny: There it is. That's Gwen's car.

11:38.431 --> 11:41.420
Sophie: Looks like it's
been there awhile.

11:41.421 --> 11:42.560
Shawn: Maybe we'll get lucky

11:42.561 --> 11:44.520
and the laptop will be here, too?

11:44.521 --> 11:46.490
I wouldn't count on it.

11:46.491 --> 11:48.540
You might want to let me go first.

11:48.541 --> 11:50.440
Why? In case there's a bomb?

11:50.441 --> 11:52.380
I mean, why would she
booby-trap her own...

11:52.381 --> 11:54.481
He's trying to protect us.

11:56.371 --> 11:57.390
It's clean.

11:57.391 --> 11:59.510
How does he know
that? How do you know that?

11:59.511 --> 12:02.560
Don't you need one of those
under-the-car mirror things

12:02.561 --> 12:05.560
or a dog who smells bombs for a living?

12:05.561 --> 12:08.400
[Grunting]

12:08.401 --> 12:09.551
It was unlocked.

12:12.431 --> 12:14.370
Danny: Yeah, I got that.

12:14.371 --> 12:16.470
There's no laptop.

12:16.471 --> 12:18.520
Shall we take to the trail?

12:18.521 --> 12:19.540
[Sighs]

12:19.541 --> 12:21.370
[Car door closes]

12:21.371 --> 12:22.684
You might want to let me go first.

12:22.709 --> 12:23.360
Yeah, we got it.

12:23.361 --> 12:24.461
[Birds chirping]

12:26.521 --> 12:29.400
You know, he's just doing his job.

12:29.401 --> 12:32.380
[Whispering] He took off his jacket.

12:32.381 --> 12:34.321
Why don't you like him? He's so nice.

12:34.322 --> 12:34.520
Looking...

12:34.521 --> 12:36.540
"Nice-looking" I think is
what you're trying to say.

12:36.541 --> 12:38.360
Oh, my God. Are you jealous?

12:38.361 --> 12:40.390
[ Scoffs ] Of that guy? He's an idiot.

12:40.391 --> 12:41.831
Actually, he's not. He went to Yale.

12:43.491 --> 12:45.480
That's not proof that he's not an idiot.

12:45.481 --> 12:47.440
He graduated summa cum laude.

12:47.441 --> 12:49.440
That's Latin for "not an idiot."

12:49.441 --> 12:50.540
Have you ever even talked to him?

12:50.541 --> 12:52.490
I'm not the one he
seems to want to talk to.

12:52.491 --> 12:53.570
Let's split up...

12:53.571 --> 12:55.481
so you two can be alone.

12:58.521 --> 13:00.380
Dan, you might want to
let me lead the way.

13:00.381 --> 13:01.480
- I'm fine.
- Oh! Ooh!

13:01.481 --> 13:03.480
[Chuckling] Oh, my gosh. Are you okay?

13:03.481 --> 13:05.360
You okay, man?

13:05.361 --> 13:07.360
[Grunts]

13:07.361 --> 13:09.490
[Flies buzzing]

13:09.491 --> 13:11.501
♪ ♪

13:13.000 --> 13:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

13:25.581 --> 13:27.561
It's Gwen.

13:31.501 --> 13:33.380
It's all been happening so quickly.

13:33.381 --> 13:35.550
We've gotten responses from
12 charities so far,

13:35.551 --> 13:37.440
but I think I've found the right one.

13:37.441 --> 13:39.360
It's called the Worldwide Women's Fund,

13:39.361 --> 13:40.530
and it's run by the
most incredible woman.

13:40.531 --> 13:42.540
[Inhales deeply] I can't
wait for you to meet her.

13:42.541 --> 13:43.560
Let's make an appointment with her.

13:43.561 --> 13:46.391
Uh, that's why I called you. She's here.

13:47.541 --> 13:49.560
Paige Baker, I'd like for you to meet...

13:49.561 --> 13:52.591
Michael Thorne.

13:54.481 --> 13:56.530
What a surprise.

13:56.531 --> 13:57.531
♪ ♪

14:01.396 --> 14:03.506
♪ ♪

14:05.526 --> 14:09.296
How do you two know each other?

14:11.436 --> 14:15.425
We recently
collaborated on a special event,

14:15.426 --> 14:18.366
but he dropped out unexpectedly.

14:20.296 --> 14:22.485
When last we spoke, you
gave me the impression

14:22.486 --> 14:25.435
you were pursuing other avenues.

14:25.436 --> 14:28.365
A misunderstanding then.

14:28.366 --> 14:31.295
I hope it doesn't get in the
way of our working together.

14:31.296 --> 14:34.325
No. Of course not.

14:34.326 --> 14:37.396
Mr. Thorne is the best at what he does.

14:39.356 --> 14:41.325
You two make quite the power couple.

14:41.326 --> 14:42.445
Oh, we're not together.

14:42.446 --> 14:44.415
Michael's my business associate.

14:44.416 --> 14:45.816
I'd set you up with him,

14:45.817 --> 14:47.435
but he's in love with another woman.

14:47.436 --> 14:49.355
- Princess.
- Is he?

14:49.356 --> 14:51.153
Yes, and he's been very
mysterious about her.

14:51.260 --> 14:52.505
He won't even tell me her name,

14:52.506 --> 14:54.435
only that she broke his heart.

14:54.436 --> 14:56.505
She broke his heart? Mm.

14:56.506 --> 14:58.425
[Cellphone ringing]

14:58.426 --> 14:59.908
Oh, that's a publicist
about the press launch.

14:59.909 --> 15:01.485
- I'll just be a moment.
- [Cellphone beeps]

15:01.486 --> 15:03.425
- Hello.
- [Footsteps depart]

15:03.426 --> 15:05.436
♪ ♪

15:08.524 --> 15:10.415
You have to leave right now.

15:10.416 --> 15:12.475
[Chuckles]

15:12.476 --> 15:15.375
You don't seem to understand, Michael.

15:15.376 --> 15:18.325
I have the power here.

15:18.326 --> 15:20.495
I can expose you to the princess.

15:20.496 --> 15:22.335
I can have you arrested.

15:22.336 --> 15:24.485
For what?

15:24.486 --> 15:25.495
You got your money back.

15:25.496 --> 15:26.816
You got your client's money back.

15:28.336 --> 15:29.516
You've got nothing on me.

15:31.416 --> 15:34.345
He's right. We need a confession.

15:34.346 --> 15:35.415
Why did you target me?

15:35.416 --> 15:37.788
I didn't target you. The
people I work with did.

15:37.892 --> 15:39.495
<i>They targeted Princess Zara, too.</i>

15:39.496 --> 15:41.305
The people he works with.

15:41.306 --> 15:42.386
Who are they?

15:43.416 --> 15:46.375
Zara: Great. Thank you.

15:46.376 --> 15:48.365
Looks like the press launch is a go.

15:48.366 --> 15:49.425
Now, what'd I miss?

15:49.426 --> 15:51.495
Just going over some logistics.

15:51.496 --> 15:54.345
Ask him to meet you
privately, away from the princess.

15:54.346 --> 15:57.455
When shall we meet to
discuss the details?

15:57.456 --> 16:01.295
I've got your number. I'll be in touch.

16:01.296 --> 16:03.306
♪ ♪

16:12.516 --> 16:15.456
You all right?

16:17.316 --> 16:18.325
You did well.

16:18.326 --> 16:19.355
Please.

16:19.356 --> 16:20.465
You got him talking.

16:20.466 --> 16:23.449
I'll stay here, follow
him in case he takes off.

16:23.600 --> 16:25.475
He won't leave. Val and
I took all his money.

16:25.476 --> 16:27.405
He'll play this con out.

16:27.406 --> 16:28.505
And when he does...

16:28.506 --> 16:30.305
we'll be there.

16:30.306 --> 16:31.787
[Sighs]

16:32.075 --> 16:33.515
Are you sure you're all right?

16:33.516 --> 16:35.516
If I was a man, would
you be asking me that?

16:37.366 --> 16:41.455
[Cellphone rings]

16:41.456 --> 16:44.375
Hey, I'm on my way back in.

16:44.376 --> 16:47.485
Oh, my God. I'll be right there.

16:47.486 --> 16:50.295
[Door opens, closes]

16:50.296 --> 16:51.920
[Indistinct chatter, telephone ringing]

16:52.036 --> 16:53.935
Valerie: We're still
waiting for the coroner's report.

16:54.082 --> 16:55.415
No, we can't wait.

16:55.416 --> 16:56.525
We have to proceed as
if this was a murder.

16:56.526 --> 16:58.455
And assume that whoever killed
Gwen has the laptop.

16:58.456 --> 16:59.525
And is either about
to use it or sell it.

16:59.526 --> 17:01.465
That's the thing.

17:01.466 --> 17:03.325
The laptop came back online an hour ago.

17:03.326 --> 17:04.444
It's masking its location,

17:04.445 --> 17:06.385
but I was able to
install a stealth program

17:06.386 --> 17:08.494
that's sending snapshots of
local wireless activity.

17:08.576 --> 17:09.298
Which means...

17:09.425 --> 17:12.415
I've narrowed the location
to a single block in Downey.

17:12.415 --> 17:14.386
- Of course you have.
- Let's go.

17:18.496 --> 17:21.295
Doors and windows are all locked.

17:21.296 --> 17:22.415
Do you see anyone inside?

17:22.415 --> 17:23.375
Nope.

17:23.376 --> 17:24.366
Danny: In that case...

17:28.376 --> 17:31.375
[Lock rattling]

17:31.376 --> 17:33.515
- You want me to, uh...
- No, Shawn. I got it. Thanks.

17:33.516 --> 17:35.395
[Sighs]

17:35.396 --> 17:36.525
- Oh!
- [Laughing] Sorry.

17:36.526 --> 17:38.375
[Sighs]

17:38.376 --> 17:39.455
How'd you get inside?

17:39.456 --> 17:42.445
Doggy door. I found the laptop, too.

17:42.446 --> 17:44.306
Okay.

17:48.376 --> 17:51.485
[Laptop beeping, clicking]

17:51.486 --> 17:54.515
It's 67% of the way through
a massive upload.

17:54.516 --> 17:57.295
- The THRUsight software?
- Most likely.

17:57.296 --> 18:00.435
Well, we can't have that.

18:00.436 --> 18:02.335
Can we?

18:02.336 --> 18:05.295
♪ ♪

18:05.296 --> 18:06.425
[Engine starts]

18:06.426 --> 18:09.670
We don't want to stick
around to catch whoever did it?

18:09.671 --> 18:12.345
- That wasn't our assignment.
- Plus, it's too dangerous.

18:12.346 --> 18:13.406
Even for you?

18:14.516 --> 18:16.515
Shawn?

18:16.516 --> 18:18.336
I see it!

18:22.376 --> 18:24.385
[Exhales sharply]

18:24.386 --> 18:25.496
Is everyone okay?

18:26.506 --> 18:29.336
Aah! Oh, my G...

18:34.376 --> 18:37.475
[Grunts]

18:37.476 --> 18:39.335
Gwen?

18:39.336 --> 18:41.486
[Breathing heavily]

18:43.040 --> 18:44.867
Gwen's alive?

18:44.996 --> 18:47.498
And prone to violence. Poor
Shawn got the worst of it.

18:47.499 --> 18:48.438
Is he all right?

18:48.439 --> 18:49.478
He's okay.

18:49.479 --> 18:50.518
Nothing can hurt that guy.

18:50.519 --> 18:52.438
But why would Gwen fake her own death?

18:52.439 --> 18:54.538
If someone was trying
to steal the software...

18:54.539 --> 18:56.428
Maybe somebody wasn't
trying to steal it.

18:56.429 --> 18:57.608
Maybe Gwen was trying to
steal it from her boss.

18:57.609 --> 18:59.548
So she can sell it on the black market?

18:59.549 --> 19:00.608
I don't think so.

19:00.609 --> 19:02.608
What are we looking at?

19:02.609 --> 19:04.759
Gwen's call history
off the burner phone.

19:04.916 --> 19:06.588
Lots of calls to the morgue.

19:06.589 --> 19:08.478
Well, that explains the
dead body she left us.

19:08.479 --> 19:09.528
Tattoo was a nice touch.

19:09.529 --> 19:11.518
What was her last outgoing call?

19:11.519 --> 19:14.578
Place called Mail, Stamp,
&amp; Ship near the airport.

19:14.579 --> 19:16.518
Lot of those places are one-stop shops

19:16.519 --> 19:18.458
for fake passports, IDs.

19:18.459 --> 19:19.468
Alice: Maybe she was planning

19:19.469 --> 19:21.468
on leaving the country with THRUsight.

19:21.469 --> 19:23.558
Valerie: Should we call the client?

19:23.559 --> 19:25.518
Listen to me. Please.

19:25.519 --> 19:28.468
You can't give THRUsight
back to Phillip Thompson.

19:28.469 --> 19:29.498
Why not?

19:29.499 --> 19:32.468
Because he's selling it to terrorists.

19:32.469 --> 19:34.588
- What?
- How do you know?

19:34.589 --> 19:36.588
When Marie and I first
sold THRUsight to Phillip,

19:36.589 --> 19:37.868
it was on the condition

19:37.869 --> 19:39.538
he tell us every client he sold it to.

19:39.539 --> 19:41.378
And he withheld that information?

19:41.379 --> 19:42.428
Not officially.

19:42.429 --> 19:43.468
As got closer to the launch,

19:43.469 --> 19:45.240
I started trolling black market sites

19:45.241 --> 19:46.578
for anything that looked like THRUsight,

19:46.579 --> 19:48.588
and I found a listing on a Tor site

19:48.589 --> 19:51.094
dedicated to illicit weapons sales.

19:51.095 --> 19:52.488
If that's true, why not
go to the authorities?

19:52.489 --> 19:55.428
Because a weapon is a
weapon no matter who has it.

19:55.429 --> 19:56.488
The DoD is everywhere.

19:56.489 --> 19:58.498
I couldn't just turn it
in or let them take it.

19:58.499 --> 20:00.498
I-I had to disappear...

20:00.499 --> 20:02.458
and take the software with me.

20:02.459 --> 20:04.488
What about Marie? Does
she know any of this?

20:04.489 --> 20:05.588
No.

20:05.589 --> 20:07.388
I-I didn't want to put her

20:07.389 --> 20:08.568
in a position to have to lie for me.

20:08.569 --> 20:12.528
Why should she have to
pay the price for this...

20:12.529 --> 20:14.498
this mess I created?

20:14.499 --> 20:16.558
I'm begging you, don't give the laptop

20:16.559 --> 20:18.429
back to Phillip Thompson.

20:20.589 --> 20:23.559
♪ ♪

20:26.379 --> 20:28.388
Where are you going?

20:28.389 --> 20:29.588
- Out.
- Dressed like that?

20:29.589 --> 20:31.468
[Scoffs] I trust there's a compliment

20:31.469 --> 20:32.588
buried in there somewhere.

20:32.589 --> 20:34.518
You look...

20:34.519 --> 20:36.378
Yes?

20:36.379 --> 20:37.519
Dangerous.

20:41.409 --> 20:42.558
Now, where you going?

20:42.559 --> 20:45.458
To solve our collection issues.

20:45.459 --> 20:46.538
Should I ask how?

20:46.539 --> 20:48.429
Probably not.

20:51.419 --> 20:53.528
[Indistinct conversations]

20:53.529 --> 20:56.578
[Piano music playing over speakers]

20:56.579 --> 20:58.589
[Footsteps approach]

21:01.529 --> 21:05.488
Look who's having a drink.

21:05.489 --> 21:06.548
Go away, darling.

21:06.549 --> 21:09.478
There's still a few hours
left till our deadline.

21:09.479 --> 21:12.609
Ticktock, ticktock... darling.

21:16.459 --> 21:18.378
Do I look worried to you?

21:18.379 --> 21:20.609
To be honest...

21:22.549 --> 21:25.378
you look pretty fit to me.

21:25.379 --> 21:27.378
[The Antlers' "Crest" plays]

21:27.379 --> 21:29.389
[Moaning]

21:36.459 --> 21:37.569
[Laughs]

21:39.499 --> 21:41.548
Oh, I really hope I
don't have to kill you.

21:41.549 --> 21:43.448
[Laughs]

21:43.449 --> 21:45.418
♪ Wait in the dark for me ♪

21:45.419 --> 21:46.588
Well, you could go rogue, you know,

21:46.589 --> 21:51.388
exercise free will, join our merry band.

21:51.389 --> 21:54.378
They'd just send a
replacement out to kill all three of us.

21:54.379 --> 21:55.428
Mm-hmm.

21:55.429 --> 21:57.598
How close are you
two to getting the money?

21:57.599 --> 21:59.609
♪ ♪

22:00.539 --> 22:02.589
Let's not ruin this, shall we?

22:05.529 --> 22:07.478
Why'd you do it?

22:07.479 --> 22:09.438
Why'd you leave the family?

22:09.439 --> 22:10.548
You were next in line.

22:10.549 --> 22:13.568
No, I was never next in line.

22:13.569 --> 22:15.538
I'm a woman.

22:15.539 --> 22:17.528
Things have changed since then.

22:17.529 --> 22:19.418
Our Benefactor's changed.

22:19.419 --> 22:21.488
Oh, really? So he's not insane anymore.

22:21.489 --> 22:23.448
I wouldn't say that.

22:23.449 --> 22:25.458
♪ Closer to truth ♪

22:25.459 --> 22:27.378
Well, that's why I left.

22:27.379 --> 22:28.508
Yes, well, you still owe money.

22:28.509 --> 22:30.578
Freedom has its price.

22:30.579 --> 22:32.468
Then it isn't freedom, isn't it?

22:32.469 --> 22:33.528
Mnh-mnh.

22:33.529 --> 22:37.508
♪ Closer to truth, but
much, much farther ♪

22:37.509 --> 22:38.549
Part of the job.

22:40.419 --> 22:42.458
The way this is part of the job?

22:42.459 --> 22:46.598
You here with me, using
sex to get what you want?

22:46.599 --> 22:48.378
Is it working?

22:48.379 --> 22:50.518
Shall we try again and find out?

22:50.519 --> 22:52.559
♪ ♪

22:59.489 --> 23:01.499
[Cellphone vibrating]

23:07.559 --> 23:09.569
[Cellphone clicks]

23:12.499 --> 23:14.418
I can't believe you actually called.

23:14.419 --> 23:16.539
We had a deal.

23:18.509 --> 23:20.018
So now you're a man of your word?

23:23.005 --> 23:25.408
If I tell you everything, if
I answer all your questions,

23:25.409 --> 23:26.538
will you please stay away?

23:26.539 --> 23:29.489
So you can do to the
princess what you did to me?

23:31.419 --> 23:33.419
So I can keep you safe.

23:36.609 --> 23:38.508
Fine.

23:38.509 --> 23:39.538
Where and when?

23:39.539 --> 23:43.549
Friday 5:00, Grand Park.

23:46.579 --> 23:49.499
I'll see you there.

23:54.499 --> 23:57.399
Come on, Alice.

23:59.599 --> 24:02.469
♪ ♪

24:10.419 --> 24:11.609
[Cellphone chimes]

24:14.016 --> 24:17.265
_

24:17.389 --> 24:19.498
[Chuckles]

24:19.499 --> 24:21.459
[Knock on door]

24:24.379 --> 24:26.498
Morning, Muzhir.

24:26.499 --> 24:28.578
He wouldn't let me ring you.

24:28.579 --> 24:29.578
Who?

24:29.579 --> 24:31.538
My brother Bashir.

24:31.539 --> 24:32.569
Zara.

24:40.589 --> 24:42.398
Who are you?

24:42.399 --> 24:44.418
I am the Princess' business advisor,

24:44.419 --> 24:45.399
Michael Thorne.

24:46.439 --> 24:48.468
The princess has no business advisor,

24:48.469 --> 24:50.378
nor has she need of one.

24:50.379 --> 24:51.271
If I may,

24:51.402 --> 24:52.598
the princess has signed legal documents

24:52.599 --> 24:56.388
establishing a foundation...

24:56.389 --> 24:58.448
♪ ♪

24:58.449 --> 25:00.389
You were saying?

25:05.697 --> 25:08.526
[Conversation in Arabic]

25:08.527 --> 25:11.607
[Indistinct conversations]

25:15.547 --> 25:16.686
Ben: Excuse me.

25:16.687 --> 25:18.607
[Gasps] Michael.

25:19.757 --> 25:22.379
I just wanted to make sure you're okay.

25:22.525 --> 25:24.666
My brother's not a bad man.

25:24.667 --> 25:25.726
He's just old-fashioned.

25:25.727 --> 25:28.556
He underestimates women,

25:28.557 --> 25:31.646
which makes him easy to manipulate.

25:31.647 --> 25:32.706
What are you up to?

25:32.707 --> 25:35.576
You and I promised
Paige Baker $15 million,

25:35.577 --> 25:36.641
and she shall have it.

25:36.647 --> 25:37.756
Now, how are you gonna manage that?

25:37.757 --> 25:40.606
By taking what you taught
me about my own finances

25:40.607 --> 25:42.707
and doing a little creative accounting.

25:44.667 --> 25:46.726
[Footsteps depart]

25:46.727 --> 25:48.606
[Keyboard clacking]

25:48.607 --> 25:50.536
[Indistinct conversations]

25:50.537 --> 25:51.716
How's Gwen?

25:51.717 --> 25:52.726
She's asleep.

25:52.727 --> 25:55.567
You guys, I found the Tor listings.

25:56.737 --> 25:59.606
"THRUsight for
sale. No questions asked."

25:59.607 --> 26:01.114
Sophie: The seller's
IP address was cloaked,

26:01.279 --> 26:02.576
but I traced it to an
encrypted data server.

26:02.577 --> 26:03.576
Where?

26:03.577 --> 26:05.696
- Olympic Edge.
- And Phillip Thompson.

26:05.697 --> 26:07.223
So Gwen was right.

26:07.375 --> 26:08.726
We were hired by the bad guys.

26:08.727 --> 26:10.596
So we can't hand over that laptop.

26:10.597 --> 26:12.686
We have to. Gwen isn't our client.

26:12.687 --> 26:15.686
Olympic Edge is our
client. We have a contract.

26:15.687 --> 26:17.526
How is this even a debate?

26:17.527 --> 26:19.646
It's not. We give the laptop back.

26:19.647 --> 26:20.646
- We can't.
- Alice.

26:20.647 --> 26:21.616
If Phillip Thompson

26:21.617 --> 26:22.616
wants it back so badly,

26:22.617 --> 26:24.646
I say that we give it to him,

26:24.647 --> 26:26.726
and we see what he does with it.

26:26.727 --> 26:30.596
Val will shake hands, collect our fee,

26:30.597 --> 26:32.666
and Phillip will
leave a satisfied customer.

26:32.667 --> 26:35.606
But after that, he'll want to
unload the software quickly,

26:35.607 --> 26:37.526
which means we'll need
to catch him in the act.

26:37.527 --> 26:38.696
So he'll be selling it to us.

26:38.697 --> 26:40.646
Which is where Sophie comes in.

26:40.647 --> 26:43.536
She will pose as an
international bidder online

26:43.537 --> 26:44.676
and make a play for the tech.

26:44.677 --> 26:46.576
We'll set up an oversees dummy account

26:46.577 --> 26:47.736
large enough to make
ourselves irresistible.

26:47.737 --> 26:49.606
And when we win the bid,

26:49.607 --> 26:51.606
we'll set up a face-to-face
for the exchange.

26:51.607 --> 26:52.676
Thompson knows all of our faces.

26:52.677 --> 26:53.756
None of us can be seen at the buy.

26:53.757 --> 26:54.686
We won't be.

26:54.687 --> 26:55.726
But we'll stay close,

26:55.727 --> 26:57.686
recording the exchange in the van

26:57.687 --> 26:59.686
while the front man brokers the sale.

26:59.687 --> 27:01.636
Who do you have in mind?

27:01.637 --> 27:02.716
[Cellphone beeps]

27:02.717 --> 27:04.729
♪ ♪

27:05.067 --> 27:06.696
I thought we didn't like this guy.

27:06.697 --> 27:09.566
You know what they say. "Keep
your friends close..."

27:09.567 --> 27:10.567
Speaking of which...

27:12.527 --> 27:13.567
They're here.

27:14.717 --> 27:16.647
Copy. I see them.

27:22.617 --> 27:23.716
Where's the man in charge?

27:23.717 --> 27:25.706
Money first.

27:25.707 --> 27:27.526
[Car door closes]

27:27.527 --> 27:28.606
[Sighs]

27:28.607 --> 27:30.736
♪ ♪

27:30.737 --> 27:33.717
[Cellphone beeping]

27:42.597 --> 27:44.577
Here we go.

27:51.607 --> 27:53.536
- Where's Phillip Thompson?
- [Car door closes]

27:53.537 --> 27:55.586
<i>I'm here on Mr. Thompson's behalf.</i>

27:55.587 --> 27:56.696
<i>And you are...</i>

27:56.697 --> 27:57.727
Marie?

27:59.727 --> 28:00.726
Take her down.

28:00.727 --> 28:04.606
Pleasure doing business.

28:04.607 --> 28:06.576
Here's the hard drive.

28:06.577 --> 28:07.697
Pleasure's all mine.

28:09.677 --> 28:10.716
Now!

28:10.717 --> 28:11.726
[Marie grunts]

28:11.727 --> 28:13.536
Get down!

28:13.537 --> 28:14.617
[Sirens wail]

28:17.627 --> 28:20.626
[Handcuffs clicking]

28:20.627 --> 28:25.566
Marie and I have been inseparable
for 10 years.

28:25.567 --> 28:26.686
How did I not see this?

28:26.687 --> 28:29.736
You were focused on your
work, saving people's lives.

28:29.737 --> 28:31.576
And she took advantage of that.

28:31.577 --> 28:33.676
And she'll pay for it... Phillip, too.

28:33.677 --> 28:35.646
I'm such an idiot.

28:35.647 --> 28:36.726
You are not.

28:36.727 --> 28:39.606
I promise this had
nothing to do with you.

28:39.607 --> 28:41.686
This was business to
them, pure and simple.

28:41.687 --> 28:43.626
So what am I supposed to do?

28:43.627 --> 28:46.124
I mean, I can't let THRUsight
out into the world.

28:46.248 --> 28:47.726
It's too late, though, isn't it?

28:47.727 --> 28:49.686
Olympic Edge has the laptop.

28:49.687 --> 28:53.626
Which has a version of the program on it

28:53.627 --> 28:56.686
that may or may not be fully functional.

28:56.687 --> 28:58.526
You corrupted the software?

28:58.527 --> 29:00.716
I built in a few safeguards.

29:00.717 --> 29:02.899
But they still have you under contract.

29:02.900 --> 29:04.170
If you run, they'll come looking,

29:04.171 --> 29:05.736
as will every other interested party.

29:05.737 --> 29:07.647
Which is why I was better off dead.

29:10.567 --> 29:12.717
Maybe we can help you with that.

29:16.577 --> 29:18.686
I'm sorry, but that was awesome.

29:18.687 --> 29:20.606
Your whole team was awesome.

29:20.607 --> 29:23.546
I'm sure you get to go on
busts like that all the time.

29:23.547 --> 29:25.746
Mostly my team and I stand around
in dark suits all day,

29:25.747 --> 29:27.546
wishing we were Danny.

29:27.547 --> 29:28.636
Say what now?

29:28.637 --> 29:30.676
Well, you actually get to
do things, solve problems.

29:30.677 --> 29:32.726
It was fun today
being a part of the team,

29:32.727 --> 29:34.647
so thank you.

29:38.677 --> 29:40.616
See? Told you he was nice.

29:40.617 --> 29:42.656
He's not nice.

29:42.657 --> 29:43.696
He's perfect.

29:43.697 --> 29:45.666
He's not perfect.

29:45.667 --> 29:47.586
How is he not perfect? Even
I'm attracted to him now.

29:47.587 --> 29:48.706
I don't know.

29:48.707 --> 29:51.566
He has too many muscles.

29:51.567 --> 29:52.666
I'm serious.

29:52.667 --> 29:54.626
Can you imagine dating a guy like that?

29:54.627 --> 29:56.706
The pressure? The upkeep?

29:56.707 --> 29:59.606
I'm sorry, you're doing just
fine in the upkeep department.

29:59.607 --> 30:02.606
Thank you?

30:02.607 --> 30:04.626
So you wouldn't date that guy?

30:04.627 --> 30:08.656
Not that he's asked, but...

30:08.657 --> 30:10.707
I don't know. Why?

30:12.577 --> 30:14.696
Just...

30:14.697 --> 30:18.617
Uh, just... curious. That's all.

30:19.697 --> 30:21.627
♪ ♪

30:31.687 --> 30:32.756
What's all this?

30:32.757 --> 30:35.716
This is how I raised the $15 million

30:35.717 --> 30:37.576
for our foundation.

30:37.577 --> 30:39.606
By selling your things?

30:39.607 --> 30:42.646
By auctioning them
online... anonymously, of course.

30:42.647 --> 30:46.626
And what Bashir doesn't
know won't hurt him...

30:46.627 --> 30:47.626
or me.

30:47.627 --> 30:50.586
Uh...

30:50.587 --> 30:52.547
They're just things.

30:53.617 --> 30:55.727
Well, you are a far
better person than I am.

30:58.707 --> 31:02.666
There was a time in my
life, perhaps even a week ago,

31:02.667 --> 31:06.526
where I thought buying all
this would make me happy.

31:06.527 --> 31:08.626
Then I met you.

31:08.627 --> 31:10.646
♪ ♪

31:10.647 --> 31:14.537
And... now it has.

31:27.166 --> 31:29.195
Gwen: This is just super-weird.

31:29.196 --> 31:31.115
I'm looking at my own tombstone.

31:31.116 --> 31:33.135
Am I making a huge mistake?

31:33.136 --> 31:35.065
You're getting a whole new life

31:35.066 --> 31:39.245
as Alison Aykle, Peace Corps volunteer.

31:39.246 --> 31:41.095
Alice: And if at any point

31:41.096 --> 31:43.075
Gwen Ericsson needs to
come back from the dead,

31:43.076 --> 31:44.236
we specialize in that, too.

31:45.256 --> 31:47.125
Thank you, guys.

31:47.126 --> 31:49.096
I'm sorry about Marie.

31:50.166 --> 31:52.125
If you ever need anything, anytime...

31:52.126 --> 31:53.236
I'll call. I promise.

31:55.036 --> 31:56.156
Bye. Bye.

31:56.157 --> 31:57.263
Bye.

32:00.066 --> 32:01.265
[Sighs]

32:01.266 --> 32:03.185
They were us, Marie and Gwen.

32:03.186 --> 32:04.235
They were just like us.

32:04.236 --> 32:08.105
They are not us, Allie.

32:08.106 --> 32:10.155
We spend all day, every day together.

32:10.156 --> 32:12.136
We tell each other everything.

32:14.166 --> 32:18.125
We're private
investigators. We have no secrets.

32:18.126 --> 32:21.085
We're not them.

32:21.086 --> 32:22.205
Thanks.

32:22.206 --> 32:24.245
[Indistinct conversations]

32:24.246 --> 32:25.256
Right.

32:28.206 --> 32:30.155
[ Sighs ]

32:30.156 --> 32:33.065
So, it is customary, when somebody dies,

32:33.066 --> 32:36.106
to throw them a wake of some kind.

32:39.066 --> 32:41.136
Do you want to maybe...

32:43.086 --> 32:44.225
get a drink?

32:44.226 --> 32:46.125
Oh.

32:46.126 --> 32:48.045
I would've loved that.

32:48.046 --> 32:52.115
Uh, but Shawn kind
of asked me to dinner.

32:52.116 --> 32:54.075
Oh.

32:54.076 --> 32:55.236
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

32:56.246 --> 32:57.245
But...

32:57.246 --> 32:59.045
No. Oh, no.

32:59.046 --> 33:00.265
It's, uh...

33:00.266 --> 33:03.065
You guys have fun.

33:03.066 --> 33:06.076
[Robert Koch's "Dreams" plays]

33:09.066 --> 33:12.246
[Man vocalizing]

33:15.156 --> 33:20.056
♪ I've been drifting ♪

33:22.036 --> 33:26.216
♪ Dreams been drifting ♪

33:28.106 --> 33:31.095
♪ I've been sifting ♪

33:31.096 --> 33:33.035
Didn't think I'd get to say goodbye.

33:33.036 --> 33:35.045
Gonna be okay back home?

33:35.046 --> 33:36.235
I'm going to be a nightmare.

33:36.236 --> 33:37.816
[Chuckles]

33:37.970 --> 33:40.125
I'm gonna make such a socially
progressive nuisance of myself,

33:40.126 --> 33:42.086
they'll have no choice but
to send me back here.

33:43.256 --> 33:46.125
But until then...

33:46.126 --> 33:51.125
♪ Exactly what I'm fighting for ♪

33:51.126 --> 33:54.235
♪ I've been mixin' up my dreams ♪

33:54.236 --> 33:55.255
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

33:55.256 --> 33:57.075
I'm not sure that's my color.

33:57.076 --> 33:58.245
It's not for you.

33:58.246 --> 34:00.155
It's for her.

34:00.156 --> 34:02.195
Your mystery woman...

34:02.196 --> 34:04.155
Give it to her.

34:04.156 --> 34:06.035
Call her.

34:06.036 --> 34:07.045
♪ Dreams ♪

34:07.046 --> 34:08.105
I can't accept this.

34:08.106 --> 34:11.155
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

34:11.156 --> 34:13.215
You deserve love.

34:13.216 --> 34:15.145
♪ Oh ♪

34:15.146 --> 34:16.155
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

34:16.156 --> 34:19.165
Bashir: Zara!

34:19.166 --> 34:21.136
♪♪

34:23.156 --> 34:26.146
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

34:28.036 --> 34:29.175
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

34:29.176 --> 34:35.145
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

34:35.146 --> 34:39.195
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

34:39.196 --> 34:40.235
[Car door closes]

34:40.235 --> 34:42.195
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

34:42.196 --> 34:47.116
- ♪ You've been switching ♪
- [Cellphone chimes]

34:49.076 --> 34:53.176
♪ Screens been switching ♪

34:55.156 --> 35:00.056
♪ You've been shifting ♪

35:01.246 --> 35:05.265
♪ Schemes been shifting ♪

35:05.266 --> 35:10.045
♪ I've been mixin' up my dreams ♪

35:10.046 --> 35:12.035
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

35:12.036 --> 35:13.215
So that's it, then.

35:13.216 --> 35:15.075
They've gone.

35:15.076 --> 35:16.115
♪ Dreams ♪

35:16.116 --> 35:18.125
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

35:18.126 --> 35:20.035
I don't suppose she gave you a check.

35:20.036 --> 35:22.065
♪ With my dreams ♪

35:22.066 --> 35:23.065
She did.

35:23.066 --> 35:25.055
But her brother froze the account.

35:25.056 --> 35:28.225
♪ Mixing my dreams ♪

35:28.226 --> 35:29.225
♪ Ooh ♪

35:29.226 --> 35:31.195
What's that? Uh...

35:31.196 --> 35:34.115
that is a gift from the princess, but...

35:34.116 --> 35:36.195
How much can we get for it?

35:36.196 --> 35:38.235
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

35:38.236 --> 35:39.236
Not enough.

35:41.156 --> 35:43.125
Can try giving it to
Felicity the collector

35:43.126 --> 35:44.165
to buy us more time.

35:44.166 --> 35:46.176
[Cellphone chimes]

35:49.046 --> 35:51.246
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

35:55.166 --> 35:58.176
♪ ♪

36:01.116 --> 36:06.195
Grand Park is
noisy, so get close to him.

36:06.196 --> 36:12.095
Stay calm, focused on your questions.

36:12.096 --> 36:14.255
If you're nervous, he'll
know it's a trap.

36:14.256 --> 36:18.066
Just keep your men
outside until I get my confession.

36:21.136 --> 36:22.255
She's on the move.

36:22.256 --> 36:25.036
[Indistinct
conversations, birds chirping]

37:30.186 --> 37:32.155
I want to know why.

37:32.156 --> 37:35.245
I need you to know I
never meant to hurt you.

37:35.246 --> 37:37.265
You just meant to bankrupt my company

37:37.266 --> 37:39.115
and steal my life savings?

37:39.116 --> 37:41.235
It's an assignment.

37:41.236 --> 37:42.235
It's a job.

37:42.236 --> 37:44.115
Yeah, I gathered that.

37:44.116 --> 37:46.075
It started as a job.

37:46.076 --> 37:48.206
It ended that way, too.

37:50.256 --> 37:53.116
I'm sorry.

37:57.206 --> 37:59.165
Why me?

37:59.166 --> 38:01.075
It wasn't you.

38:01.076 --> 38:02.155
It was your firm.

38:02.156 --> 38:04.105
I was supposed to come in as a client.

38:04.106 --> 38:06.125
It was supposed to last three months,

38:06.126 --> 38:07.165
and then I'd be gone.

38:07.166 --> 38:09.126
But you got greedy.

38:12.136 --> 38:14.076
That's not what happened.

38:18.096 --> 38:20.055
I was going to tell you everything.

38:20.056 --> 38:21.201
I tried.

38:23.587 --> 38:26.195
Then I asked you to get on a
plane with me and disappear.

38:26.196 --> 38:27.225
Do you remember that?

38:27.226 --> 38:30.215
♪ ♪

38:30.216 --> 38:33.043
We'll go to City
Hall, and we'll get married.

38:33.056 --> 38:34.861
Then we'll get on a
plane, and we will go

38:34.862 --> 38:36.085
wherever you want to go.

38:36.086 --> 38:38.045
We'll go where no one can find us.

38:38.046 --> 38:41.035
♪ ♪

38:41.036 --> 38:42.215
Ben: I had to make a choice...

38:42.216 --> 38:47.185
either stay with the
people I work for...

38:47.186 --> 38:49.256
or leave with you, and I chose you.

38:53.116 --> 38:55.076
It was real.

38:56.216 --> 38:59.176
What we had was real.

39:05.156 --> 39:07.056
And I love you.

39:09.126 --> 39:12.085
♪ ♪

39:12.086 --> 39:15.076
<i>That's why I'm here today, and
that's what I have to say.</i>

39:27.136 --> 39:29.226
Nothing else matters.

39:36.156 --> 39:38.076
As far as your firm is concerned...

39:54.106 --> 39:56.116
[Mouths words]

40:11.196 --> 40:13.065
This fantasy you have

40:13.066 --> 40:15.095
that I'm a con man who's
after your money

40:15.096 --> 40:17.185
<i>is pathetic</i>

40:17.186 --> 40:21.255
and desperate...

40:21.256 --> 40:24.226
beneath you, and you need to let it go.

40:27.116 --> 40:29.055
You need to let me go.

40:29.056 --> 40:31.215
All agents, move in.

40:31.216 --> 40:34.245
♪ ♪

40:34.246 --> 40:36.266
[Mouths words]

40:41.368 --> 40:43.255
Guys, head south to park and Grand.

40:43.256 --> 40:45.165
<i>- [Static hisses]
- Woman: Copy that.</i>

40:45.166 --> 40:47.105
You let him just walk away?

40:47.106 --> 40:48.145
The only reason he walked away

40:48.146 --> 40:49.797
is because you and
your men barged in here

40:49.798 --> 40:51.065
before I got my confession!

40:51.066 --> 40:52.105
He was fleeing the scene.

40:52.106 --> 40:54.085
You were gonna arrest
him on what grounds?

40:54.086 --> 40:57.075
You don't seem too
upset to have lost him.

40:57.076 --> 40:58.265
Really?

40:58.266 --> 41:00.156
I don't seem upset to you?

41:02.186 --> 41:05.175
You want to blame somebody,

41:05.176 --> 41:07.135
you blame yourself.

41:07.136 --> 41:08.195
I did my part.

